250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 cup Marinara Sauce
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
1 tbsp Balsamic Vinegar
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
¾ tbsp Sugar*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and sausage. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add marinara, pesto, half the vinegar and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant and slightly thickened.

Meanwhile, halve tomatoes.
In a medium bowl, whisk together remaining vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. (NOTE: This is your salad dressing!)

On a foil-lined baking sheet, arrange buns cut-sides up.
Spread buns with 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter.
Broil buns for 1-2 min, in the middle of the oven, until toasted. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Divide sausage mixture between bottom buns. Sprinkle half the Parmesan over top and return to the oven.
Broil bottom buns for 1-2 min, in the middle of the oven, until cheese melts slightly.
When done, place top buns over top.
To the bowl with dresssing (from step 2), add tomatoes and arugula and spinach mix. Toss to coat.
Divide sandwiches and salad between plates.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over salad.